title: Mike Kelly (Pennsylvania politician)
added: After [[Donald Trump]] lost the [[2020 United States presidential election in Pennsylvania|2020 presidential election in Pennsylvania]] and refused to concede, and spread falsehoods and conspiracy theories about fraud, Kelly aided Trump in trying to overturn the election results. Kelly filed a lawsuit seeking to invalidate more than 2.5 million legally cast votes. The [[Pennsylvania Supreme Court]] unanimously rejected Kelly's suit, additionally ruling to "[[dismiss with prejudice]]."
